      "span_text": "The NA from H3N2 viruses has been reported to be more stable than N1 and thus the relatively constant signal observed for N2 NA could be due to the protein's better stability.  In any case, this analysis appears to support the notion that NA content in commercial vaccines is highly variable,  although such a conclusion cannot be drawn without quantification using a calibration standard."
